Ethereum Name Service (ENS) was launched on Ethereum in May 2017. The service provided by ENS is to map user-defined domain names with .eth suffix to user addresses. For example, when users need to transfer money, they can transfer money by simply entering vitalik.eth without entering complicated wallet addresses. When using wallets such as Little Fox to connect to the website, the user's ENS domain name will also be displayed directly on the front end. Each ENS address is an ERC721 NFT that can be traded in NFT trading markets such as Opensea.

ENS's domain name service is priced according to the character length of the domain name.

